                                                   Snehasish hearing   Rugby meet   Chirag practice
                      
	 The Indian Football Association (IFA) players status committee, on Saturday, decided to send the original documents of East Bengals contract with Snehasish Chakraborty to a handwriting expert.         
	Snehasish had earlier alleged that East Bengal had forged his signature on the contract papers in their bid to prevent him from playing for Mohun Bagan in the ensuing season.         
	We have listened to both Snehasish and East Bengal and have decided to refer the matter to a hand-writing expert to look whether Snehasishs allegations are right or not, players status committee chairman Pradip Bose said after a two-hour long meeting, attended by Snehasish and the East Bengal officials.         
	The committee will again meet on Thursday after obtaining the report.                     
	 Armenian College outsmarted Kolkata Police 22-5 in a division-I match of the Calcutta Cup Rugby Tournament, held at the CC amp;FC, on Saturday. In a division-II match, Sergent Institute defeated Maidan Hazard 10-3.                     
	 Chirag United had a two-hour long training session under Brazilian trainer Garcia at Central Park on Saturday. Besides, physical training the players underwent a medical test on the day when Ashim Biswas was absent. This was their first day of training this season.                       
	SNOOKER: State championship finals at the BRC from 3pm                                                                                                                       
